          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill creates a zero-interest loan program for certain federal and District of Columbia employees impacted by a federal government shutdown. Specifically, banks enrolled in the program must offer zero-interest loans, subject to a maximum per-person limit, to&nbsp;such individuals during the first 90 days of a shutdown.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-02-13T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
    <title>To create a zero interest loan program for Federal and District of Columbia employees furloughed or excepted from such furlough during a lapse in Federal appropriations, and for other purposes.</title>
